  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Yaki is the starting Magi.  This magi lets your creatures attack twice a turn.  Get out your creatures and begin to attack with as much as you can early.  The other magi can hold their own but the early beatdown is what can win games.  If you let the opponent get some big beefy guys out you will be struggling.  I have been playing this deck for the longest time (since the game came out) and it has proved to be really good.  There are not a lot of rares so the deck is easy to build.   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
